actual.comment:
'-Health, Safety and Environment (HSE) Gap Analysis consultancy service is finalized, the final consultation workshop is undertaken;
-Consultancy services for the preparation of a CBA for the use of natural gas and low carbon fuels in the transport sector in Lebanon was awarded to ILF Business Consult GMBH and works commenced in June 2015;
-Procurement of consultancy services for the preparation of a National Oil Spill Contingency Plan has undergone a long negotiations process, and contract with selected company is under signature;
-Participated in the International Association for Impact Assessment Conference in April 2015 on the social, economic, and environmental impacts of the oil and gas sector;
-Held continuous meetings with the Norwegian Counterparts under the Oil for Development Program to discuss SODEL outcomes (peer review), areas of collaboration, and to plan for training courses in 2015;
-Continuous coordination with the relevant committee in the Ministry of Environment to follow up on SODEL activities, common needs, and future work plans.

-Construction works of the Roman amphitheater as well as the guard house and public toilets are completed;
-Completed around 95% of the internal roads of the public park; 
-Completed the construction of the upstand for the fence around the landfill and fence installation is underway;
-Completed the construction of two irrigation water tanks (50m3 each), and irrigation network is being installed; 
-Three Pergolas and bridge are being completed;
-Completed 90% of lighting poles and electrical fixtures;
-Planted around 200 trees and plantation of different types (citrus, cocus, pines, olives, etc.).

target.comment:
-The inception workshop is organized and the project is officially launched;
-The current energy context is defined; A root-cause analysis, identification of bottlenecks and solutions to the NEEREA process (loan process to be adopted by the private sector) are proposed; Status of net-metering and Feed in Tariff (FiT) are defined and related policies with required legal and regulatory reforms adapted to the Lebanese context are developed based on experience (barriers and solutions) in other countries (Europe). 
-Requirements/criteria of pilot demonstration projects are defined and related application is prepared;
-The services of a local consultant are procured to conduct a Decentralised Renewable Energy  survey and to create the national baseline.

actual.comment:
'-Inception Workshop successfully organized on 29 January 2015 with the participation of national counterparts and main stakeholders (EU, Ministry of Energy and Water, Private Sector, Council for development and Reconstruction, GEF/UNDP Regional Technical Advisor etc);
-The root-cause analysis, identification of bottlenecks and solutions to the NEEREA process (loan process to be adopted by the private sector) is completed; The Feed-in-Tariff and De-risking Analysis Study is initiated, as well as the Renewable Energy Grid Code study;
-Enabling environment for the implementation of the pilot demonstration projects is set through the following: Modality of the Grant/Loan and application form is finalized and launched with the Banque du Liban; the Expression of Interest for companies is completed;
-Renewable Energy Market Monitoring methodology work is initiated by meeting all stakeholders and by designing the data model.
